gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Knicks 128, 76ers 92
gameRecap.excerpt: The Knicks defeated the 76ers, 128-92, as they won their third consecutive game and improved to 20-15 on the year. Jalen Brunson led New York with 29 points as Quentin Grimes (19 points, eight rebounds) and Isaiah Hartenstein (17 points, six rebounds, five assists) totaled 36 points. Joel Embiid led Philadelphia with 30 points, 10 rebounds, and three assists while Tyrese Maxey added 27 points and nine assists. The 76ers moved to 23-11 with the loss.
